gs.  I am the Dark Elf  Deganota, Rogue of the 22nd Dagger.  I am petitioning for a joining of theViolent Harvest.  I will be expecting an Emissary as soon as possible.  Please do not insult me by sending a pathetic male.<br>
<br>
Deganota<br>
22nd Dagger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufaeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/28/01 6:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> You have little grounds to make any demands from the Harvest.  If we send a male, if we send a bixie, you should be honored that the Chosen of Innoruuk have taken note of you whatsoever.  As far as us sending an emissary upon command, then you have much to learn about respect and your place in this world.  You will find many willing teachers among us, should we bother to even acknowledge you further.  If you wish to learn more about us, then you will seek out the Dread Overlord Xareth.  I will speak for Dread Overlord Ueudiinya as well as myself when I say that we will not converse with you until you have proven yourself worthy of even a culling quest. <p>Faeolin R'Danya<BR>
Champion of 54 Battles<BR>
<BR>
<center><img src="http://www.violentharvest.com/sigs/Fae_Sig.jpg"  border=0> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udeganota.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deganota</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/28/01 8:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> I am Dark Elf and not only am I Dark Elf but I am Female thus giving me the right of command over the simple males of our species as well as the rest of the frail, pathetic creatures other pitiful gods decided to create.  It is my birthright and I accept it with full measure.  <br>
I am a Dark Elf female and as such even those males who, though possibly stronger than myself momentarily, I associate myself must know their place.  As a daughter of Innoruk I will not relent my birthright due to some pale-world idealism.  You either accept me for my strength as a daughter of hatred or you do not.  I will not debase myself by raising males above their status.  <br>
<br>
Deganota<br>
Rogue of the 22nd Dagger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ukhasirath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khasirath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.violentharvest.com/sigs/vh_anim.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dire Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/28/01 8:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/khasface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> The Dire Overlord, Knight of Innoruuk's Will, steps forward.  Heavy armour in the colours of shadows and blood encase his body, though his head is left bare, his moon-white hair bound at the nape of his neck, the long strands flowing almost to his belt.  A shadowed mace hangs at his hip, a finely forged longblade of mithril is sheathed in its baldric across his back, and slung across his back is a thick shield sheathed in the bones of Ashenbone Drakes.  Upon his face there is a sanguine rune-like sigil, a sword of thorns.  His violet eyes narrow as he focuses intensely upon Deganota.<br>
<br>
His voice is low and controlled as he speaks, &quot;I do not care what the traditions of your own House may be, petitioner.  As of yet you have shown nothing but a childish sense of entitlement to the Harvest.  If ye are to be judged in your hate to see if you are worthy of serving in the Father's Army, then ye shall bow to those of greater station, female and male alike.<br>
<br>
&quot;In Neriak the Queen and King each rule as equals.  Innoruuk is male, and we all bow first to Him.  Do not seek to force your matriarchal ways upon others, for you only dishonor yourself.  Among the Chosen, and the majority of Teir'Dal, females and males serve as equals, their status determined by their hate and their honor, not their gender.<br>
<br>
&quot;If that is perfectly clear to you, then you have a choice to make.  Present yourself to Dread Overlord Xareth to begin your Culling, or leave this Grange-house now.  I will not stand for such churlish backtalk to one of my Dread Overlords.&quot;<br>
<br>
He begins to turn away, then spins on his heel to face the young Rogue again. &quot;And one more thing, child.  I would know the name of your House.  Ye profess to be of an age when most Houses allow their children to wear their name, but you have not declared it.  I would know which House comes before the Harvest with such disgraceful words.&quot; <p><center><a href="http://www.violentharvest.com"><img src="http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/khas_sig.jpg"></a><br>
  Email me at: <a href="mailto:fractalcodec@aol.com">fractalcodec@aol.com</a></center>
<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ukhasirath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khasirath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.violentharvest.com/sigs/vh_anim.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/28/01 9:05:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uvresk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vresk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ambassador to Kunark</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/29/01 7:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> Vresk loped into the Grange, looking for something to do.  Checking through the various rooms, he stopped by the area where people petition to join the guild, which seemed an area of uncommon activity.<br>
<br>
Upon entering, he immediately noticed the Dire Overlord in confrontation with another Teir'Dal he did not know.  The monk assumed it was another petitioner.  However, Khasirath's manner and bearing were one of anger and confrontation, suggesting a possible enemy.  Vresk shifted his weight slightly, readying his body for combat if necessary.  The magical brand of the Dragon of Hate on his arm pulsed and writhed in response.<br>
<br>
The Iksar calmly strode over to the bulletin board, which allowed him to listen in on the conversation without seeming nosy.  Within moments he was fighting a chuckle.  Mating rituals.  Again.  Do the Teir'Dal argue about anything else?<br>
<br>
Turning from his spot, Vresk walked over to his friend and laid what he hoped was a calming claw on his shoulder.  Beaming a smile (a disturbing sight at the very least, not many greeted a mouthful of sharp teeth as welcoming) at the petitioner, he spoke in Teir'Dal, &quot;Dark tidingss, Petitioner.  We are honored to have you in our Grange.&quot;  Khasirath shot him a dangerous look, which he ignored.  &quot;Your being here iss evidencce that you are intelligent and wisse enough to know that the Harvesst will come, ssweeping asside the lessser people'ss and placcing the Teir'Dal (and their alliess) in their proper placcess.<br>
<br>
&quot;We assure you, however, that your pressencce in the guild iss not neccesssary.  Innoruuk will guide the Harvesst bassed on your devotion to Him,&quot; the monk allowed the stress on the last word sink in.  &quot;If you wish to join the Violent Harvesst as a guild, then I ssuggesst you learn to resspect your future ssissterss and brotherss, for doing otherwisse createss disscord.  We don't like disscord within our rankss.  It hamperss our efficienccy.  I'm ccertain you undersstand.&quot;<br>
<br>
His speech finished, he bowed to the newcomer, and then even lower to the Dire Overlord, respecting the latter's station, then stepped back to allow the pair to continue their conversation. <p><img src=http://starwave.smartdesk.net/www/kooK/vresk1.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ushaedewavecaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaede Wavecaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Harvester</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/29/01 10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> Shaede sat quietly unseen at the back of the central hall of the Grange, her air elemental hovering silently in front of her.  A minor cantrip changed the temperature of the elemental to mask her body with a uniform heat the same as the rear wall.   Her quiet contemplation was shattered by the voices of those in the room at the end of the hall.  With an irritated sigh she waited for the distractions to leave.  A few minutes later she watched as the Dire Overlord and the Ambassador left.  Standing quickly, she walked into the room with the Rogue, her elemental silent and invisible behind her.<br>
<br>
Walking in she faced the Rogue; at her silent command her elemental floated up to engulf Shaede, the invisible winds of its body whipping her hair about.  “Congratulations, you have managed to get on the bad side of not only one of our most dangerous Dread Overlords, but also managed to bring an edge to the voice of one of our most collected.”<br>
<br>
The smile on her lips was welcoming and deadly.  A dangerous look to her eye spoke of sanity barely held.<br>
<br>
“I am the Matron of House K`Thalion.  You will do well to remember the name of my House.  You will also do well to be careful of those you incite within the Harvest; the Dire Overlord has powerful allies as well as courtesans.  But please, do not count me as an enemy.  I like your... attitude.  I would like to speak with you more, but my time does not allow it at the moment.  Please, seek me out so that we may speak more.”<br>
<br>
Shaede turned, her hair calming as her elemental flowed away from her on the air currents.  She turned, her eyes dark and clouded.<br>
<br>
“I will stand as your sponsor.  But I will warn you.  Should you make enemies within the guild, count me as one of them.  This is my family, these are my friends, and I will slay any who stand against us....”<br>
<br>
The room was once again empty, save for the new petitioner.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udeganota.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deganota</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/30/01 5:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> Deganota watched as the three came and spoke then left.  Calling on the Father she faded into the darkness to contemplate.<br>
<br>
Decision made she drew the sword turned, by her hand, to the Fathers will.  Whispering one of his Lesser Names she sets it to a blaze and with a prayer writes her words in the air...<br>
<br>
Shaede, I did not come here to make enemies.  I came to do the Father's bidding and had hopes that such could be accomplished with greater efficiency within these hallowed walls.  I do not say I will not interact with males nor did I say I would not be TOLERANT of these males for there are times when necessity deems such to be so.<br>
<br>
I have offered my talents and my wisdom BUT I do have my ethics and will defend them with my life. We, made by the father, are the nurturers and the keepers of all he holds holy.  Males, though inconvenient, are many times a necessity.  I do not hold in high regard a species that when I slip out of my tunic stumble during battle.<br>
<br>
I have no qualms about using ALL the talents I posses to obtain the goals which the Father sets before me.  To believe that males and females fight side by side out of MUTUAL agreement is abhorrent and a disgrace to the power the Father has given us in the creation and destruction of life.  WE bear the seeds of his followers.  WE tend the growth and the teaching of his followers, our people.  The very idea that males are equal is a pale-skinned idea.  Probably derived from those filthy humans who seem to have taken up residence over most of the world.<br>
<br>
The fact that we live beneath the world is proof of a Males inadequacies.  Were it not for them we would have ruled this world LONG ago.  Them and their foolish tempers and their &quot;We fight now&quot; rather than temper it with patience and planning have set us back far too long. My belief in this will not be swayed.<br>
<br>
The Iksar, whom I know not, is somewhat of an enigma to me.  I know very little of them and have little against them.<br>
<br>
I am surely interested in the joining yet I will not allow the facts to be clouded by anyone's brute strength.<br>
<br>
I will find you and, if you are still amiable to speak, would be more than happy to speak with you.<br>
<br>
As for my House, that I will tell you when and if we speak.<br>
<br>
I mean no insult to the women of the dark and my petition was just that, a request for joining.   My only request was that I would be greeted not by a male but by one who holds true power.<br>
<br>
Till we meet, Skleave' Noctura<br>
<br>
Daughter of HIM<br>
Deganota<br>
Rogue of the 22nd Dagger<br>
<br>
<br>
Finished writing, Deganota calls upon the Father and sets her words burning in the air.  She wills her sword to fade into the darkness and leaves an echoing whisper...Remember, remember....  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ujeckss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JecksS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiller</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/30/01 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> Watching from the shadows, unseen as usual, Jecks wonders what House T'Rhennic would think of this woman and her demands. <p>Jecks Shadowleaf<BR>
52nd Season Pathfinder of Hate<BR>
Dark Stalker of the Violent Harvest<BR>
<center><img src="http://www.violentharvest.com/sigs/Jecks_Sig.jpg"border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ushaedewavecaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaede Wavecaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Harvester</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/30/01 9:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Petition of Joining</span><hr size=1> Shaede laughed.<br>
<br>
With a minor incantation the letter burst into flames.  She pulled out quill and parchment and penned a letter, tears of humor streaked her cheeks.<br>
<br>
&quot;The FATHER's bidding, hmmmm.  Interesting for someone who does not believe in the strength of males. If your prideful ignorance will not allow you to speak with or RESPECT males then turn now and go find another Guild to soil with your outdated and almost lightborn prejudice.  I will not tolerate any member being this blind and I assure you neither will any of the others. If you think mere nudity would sway any of our members then you are uneducated as well as ignorant.  I have seen much better looking distractions not turn the blade of the General of Empire, the Dread Overlord and my chosen Xareth, nor the Dire Overlord Khasirath.<br>
<br>
We may bear the soil NOT the seeds.  If you understood things properly, the soil is nothing without the seed.  Maybe you should join Vresk on his research of mating?<br>
<br>
In your words and beliefs you have offended me.  In your ignorance you disgrace the Teir`Dal race.  I will not see you join us if you do not cast away these ideals born in prejudice.  You are no better then the lightblind that would deny one because of the color of their skin.<br>
<br>
Go now, and try to succeed without a family.<br>
<br>
Shaede K`Thalion<br>
