<br>
Though she could understand the womans sentiments. Ferals reason for distrusting the males where naut as the rogue's. Her words gave Feral pause as slender fingers stilled upon the blade. Her words made Feral wonder where they had been taught. For as long as Feral could remember she'd naut had a &quot;house&quot;. And look, she thought, she'd turned out just fine. What need did one have of a fancy house? Was it naut but a name to be either upheld or besmirched? Feral really did'nt care who her family had been. She'd stand on her own name or not at all.<br>
<br>
Turning away from the conversations, Feral continued to ply cloth to blade. The smile growing to one of pure malicious amusement. When Feral had joined and spouted her own view, It was simply for the fun of stirring things up. Though she had Khasirath believe she actually wanted his command. Another shrug, well, with those words burned into his mind, he's naut sure to forget her was he? A sound escaped from her and she stiffend. By the shadows, was it actually a giggle? <br>
<br>
The rogue needed to really use her head instead of her pride if she wanted to gain respect and a place among the Harvest. Most fools knew when to keep their mouths shut and their views to themselves, those who didn't ended up dead. <br>
<br>
As the room emptied, Feral remained. Watching the antics of those who came and went. Still unnoticed and really not caring if any did. Almost lovingly she slid the blade back into its sheath. That really was all anyone needed for themselves. <br>
<br>
