<br>
Her eyes glitter as she reads it. When she is finished she sets her blade against it and turns it to ash... then prepares her response...<br>
<br>
Shaede Wavecaller,<br>
<br>
Obviously the nude analogy was an extreme to making a point which, I wonder, was received. Lightborn prejudice? I believe that the Lightborn work together with their males and even ENCOURAGE working together with their males. This is NOT a Lightborn prejudice, this is OUR way, almost forgotten it would seem. I did not deny their usefulness, I just deny their belief that they may command us. US, the bearers of life! We bring about their existence and for that alone, not counting many other reasons, are they beholden to us. That is the LEAST of many.<br>
<br>
There have been very few, VERY few males in our entire history that deserve the respect of a woman. As of this generation I have not found any. Mayhap the one you defend is such? Of this I do not know for I know him not. Does he treat YOU with the proper respect or has he too fallen from the true ways of our people?<br>
<br>
Only one of our males have I EVER encountered that even came CLOSE to respecting the old ways and I have not seen him in a long time. Daiunus, I wonder what became of him? Perhaps even he has fallen to the lightborn ways of commanding women. Ne'er did he demand that I give him respect he did not earn, nor had he ever approached ME without showing proper respect. Tis one of many. A shame there are so few.<br>
<br>
You claim that it is *I* who is ignorant? Interesting coming from one who claims the lightborn races judge us by our skin. They do not judge us by our skin, FAR from it. They judge us by our history and their fear. We were once a ruling power they feared. They respected our strength and would fall prostrate to the ground when we would pass. Now, no longer. Now they shun us out of fear and jealousy of our old power. They now treat us like a common street urchin and fling us from their cities. It is not our skin they judge us against. Find your history. When you do, tell me who was in power?<br>
<br>
Deganota<br>
<br>
P.S. Interesting there are no &quot;Mad&quot; Prophetesses' don't you think?<br>
<br>
<br>
Deganota's sword flares in response to her anger. So much forgotten, so much to be done.<br>
<br>
